            <scopecontent id="aspace_860985a993c191223461fad86cf568b4">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Most correspondence consists of letters from Moreno to Gaston Baheux. Circa 450 letters to Baheux are present, concerning their friendship, Moreno's work in theater and films during the 1930s-1940s, and other subjects including Colette, Moreno's home, in Touzac, her relationship with Pierre Moreno and his wife Micheline Moreno, and experiences during World War II.</p>
               <p>Other correspondence includes letters to Moreno from Eugène Morand, concerning performances of <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                     <part>Hamlet</part>
                  </title> in a French translation by Morand and Marcel Schwob.</p>
            </scopecontent>
